## Implementation Plan (Phased)

### Phase 0: TDD Tests (Step 0)
1. **Created `tests/web/test_games_page.py`** — comprehensive test suite covering all phases:
   - **`TestGamesManagementAPI`** (10 tests): GET `/api/games-management` — empty list, metadata, line/char counts, linking status (deck_id/vndb/anilist), sorting, dates, genres/tags/links, auto-create orphans, games with no lines
   - **`TestGamesGridSorting`** (1 test): `?sort=last_played` query param — will fail until Phase 1 sort param is implemented
   - **`TestGamesPageRoute`** (2 tests): GET `/games` returns 200 + HTML — will fail until template is created
   - **`TestNavigation`** (1 test): navigation.html contains `/games` link — will fail until nav is updated
   - **`TestGameDetailRoute`** (2 tests): GET `/game/<id>` returns 404/200 — will fail until template is created
   - **`TestCreateGame`** (6 tests): POST `/api/games` — success, missing/empty title, no body, duplicate, orphan linking
   - **`TestUpdateGame`** (7 tests): PUT `/api/games/<id>` — field updates, 404, no data, manual overrides, vndb prefix, completed, genres/tags
   - **`TestMarkGameComplete`** (2 tests): POST `/api/games/<id>/mark-complete` — success + 404
   - **`TestDeleteGame`** (4 tests): DELETE unlink (preserves lines) + permanent delete (removes lines) + edge cases
   - **`TestOrphanedGames`** (2 tests): GET `/api/orphaned-games` — no orphans + finds orphans
   - **`TestGamesTableModel`** (22 tests): Model unit tests — CRUD, get_by_*, get_or_create, completed/in_progress, dates, lines, fuzzy matching, manual overrides, links, defaults
   - **`TestGameLinesForGamesFeature`** (4 tests): GameLinesTable behaviors the feature relies on
   - **`TestPlaceholderImage`** (2 tests): empty image string vs data URI
2. Uses in-memory SQLite DB per test (autouse fixture), Flask test client, no external deps
3. Run with: `pytest tests/web/test_games_page.py -v`

### Phase 0.5: Bug Fix (COMPLETED)
1. **Fix broken import** in `texthooking_page.py:1107` - changed `util.games_table` to `util.database.games_table`

### Phase 1: API Adjustment + Games Grid Page
1. **Use existing `/api/games`** from `game_management_routes.py` for the grid. It already returns all needed fields (id, image, titles, type, difficulty, completed, last_played, line_count, mined_character_count, genres, tags, links, etc.). Only change needed: **add a `sort` query param** (default `last_played`) so the grid can request `?sort=last_played`.
2. Add "Games" link to navigation component (`components/navigation.html`) - insert between "Search" and "Database Management"
3. Add `/games` route to `texthooking_page.py`
4. Create `templates/games.html` - 4-column responsive grid with:
   - **Search/filter bar** at top: text input that filters games by title (original/romaji/english) client-side
   - Grid of game cards: cover image (or GSM favicon placeholder) + game name below
   - Click handler: navigate to `/game/{uuid}`
5. Create `static/css/games.css` - grid layout styles, search bar styles
6. Create `static/js/games.js` - fetch `/api/games`, render grid, wire up search filter
7. **Placeholder image**: use `/static/favicon-96x96.png` for games with no cover image
8. **UI States**:
   - **Loading**: Show spinner while fetching games (reuse `.loading-indicator` pattern from database page)
   - **Empty**: Show "No games found" message with link to Database Management page
   - **Error**: Show error message with retry button if API call fails
   - **No search results**: Show "No games match your search" when filter returns zero results

### Phase 2: Game Detail Page (game_stats.html)
1. The `/game/<game_id>` route already exists in `texthooking_page.py:1104` (import now fixed)
2. Create `templates/game_stats.html` - game detail page with navbar
3. Create `static/css/game-stats.css` - detail page styles
4. Create `static/js/game-stats.js` - fetch `/api/game/{id}/stats`, render page
5. **Replicate Overview page's game info box** (from `overview.html` lines 22-152):
   - Game cover image (or GSM favicon placeholder) + titles (original, romaji, english)
   - Type badge, description with expand/collapse
   - Links pills, genres pills, tags pills
   - Completion progress bar
   - **Overall Game Statistics** grid: Characters, Chars/Hour, Time Spent, Est. Time Left
   - **Do NOT include**: session navigation (prev/next arrows), delete session button,
     current session stats section, "Today's Sessions" header
6. Settings cog icon that opens management actions dropdown
7. **UI States**:
   - **Loading**: Show skeleton/spinner while fetching game data
   - **404/Error**: Show "Game not found" or error message with back-to-games link

### Phase 3: Settings Cog / Game Management on Detail Page
1. Add settings cog UI (dropdown menu) to game_stats.html
2. **Edit game metadata** - port edit modal from database page (`database.html` lines 504-651, `database-game-data.js`)
3. **Link/unlink** to jiten.moe/VNDB/AniList - port linking functionality (reuse `unified-search.js`)
4. **Mark as completed** toggle - simple `PATCH` to update `completed` field
5. **Re-pull metadata** from linked sources
6. **Merge games** - searchable game picker UI:
   - Settings cog dropdown has "Merge other games into this one" option
   - Opens a modal with a **searchable list** of all other games (fetched from `/api/games`)
   - User searches/selects one or more games to merge INTO the current game (current game = target)
   - This is simpler than the bulk operations approach since the target is always the current game
   - Selected games shown in a list with remove buttons, then "Confirm Merge" button
   - Confirmation modal (reuse pattern from `database.html` lines 654-714): shows target game (green) vs source games (warning) with stats
   - Calls `POST /api/merge_games` with `{ target_game: current_game.title_original, games_to_merge: [selected_names] }`
   - On success: refresh the game detail page stats

